INSERT INTO `sportgrounds_and_parks_collections` VALUES (1,'v1khdhqlzms4re620y0x62r5','Reprovisioning of Harbour Road Sports Centre and Wan Chai Swimming Pool (Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1126)','Reprovisioning of Harbour Road Sports Centre and Wan Chai Swimming Pool','MTR Corporation Limited','20 January 2014 - 31 May 2017','<p>Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a 17km-long railway line expansion undertaken by MTR Corporation in Kowloon and Hong Kong Island. The project involves stretching the line from Tai Wai to Hung Hom and Hung Hom to Admiralty sections, linking a number of existing railway lines passing through several districts in Hong Kong</p><p>The SCL Exhibition Station is located under the existing Wan Chai Ferry Pier Public Transport Interchange, Harbour Road Sports Centre (HRSC) and Wan Chai Swimming Pool (WCSP). As the station were to be constructed using the cut-and-cover method, the HRSC and WCSP had to be permanently relocated to the old public car park in the south. The existing facilities were demolished only after the reprovisioning work is completed.</p><p>The scope of the project comprised the construction of the new HRSC and WCSP, a 5-storey RC building with steel trussed roof. Associated with the new building, the scope is also included the design and construction of the external building envelope; design and construction of internal fabric and finishes, equipment and fittings; design and construction of building services works, including, among others, hoisting beams and support details, steelwork access platforms, electrical, ELV, filtration, ACMV, FS, lift &amp; escalator, Town Gas and plumbing and drainage systems.</p>','2025-06-03 03:42:41.826000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.738000',NULL,8,36,'en',1.00),(3,'xe55cwszwozb2a6hl0yuryep','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area (Contract No. CV/2011/02)','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 September 2011 - 31 December 2014','<p>This is a Design and Build project for the uplifting works to promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area. The objective of the works is to enhance the Aberdeen area and aim to further bring out the unique features of &#x27;traditional fishing harbour&#x27; and the local culture of Aberdeen and, by reinforcing the elements of diversified tourism, to enhance Aberdeen&#x27;s attractiveness to both international visitors and local residents.</p>','2025-06-03 03:43:43.133000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.690000',NULL,8,36,'en',2.00),(5,'fmttx9snlu7y3jxrzdkvjjnd','Thrill Mountain & Polar Adventure (Ocean Park Master Redevelopment Project Contract No. CS03)','Thrill Mountain & Polar Adventure','Ocean Park Corporation','02 November 2009 - 08 July 2012','<p>Ocean Park&#x27;s Master Redevelopment Plan included two new themed projects in &quot;The Summit&quot; area - &quot;Thrill Mountain&quot; and &quot;Polar Adventure&quot;, covering a total area of 400,000 square feet.</p><p>&quot;Thrill Mountain&quot; offered six attractions, booth games, as well as food, beverages and merchandise, while &quot;Polar Adventure&quot; consists of &quot;North Pole Encounter&quot;, &quot;South Pole Spectacular&quot; and &quot;Arctic Blast &quot;.</p><p>Several building materials used in the construction included fiberglass reinforced concrete for the manufacture of icebergs and imitation stones. In order to allow visitors to have the best underwater experience, the exhibition hall used transparent acrylic plates and transparent tempered glass of 202mm thickness for the construction of underwater tunnels and underwater screen. The newly opened restaurant also used transparent acrylic panel for the screen, allowing visitors to watch the Antarctic penguins while enjoying their food.</p>','2025-06-03 03:44:40.338000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.755000',NULL,8,36,'en',3.00),(7,'f7mfjaga2i0kjuemvscbb1up','Vet Hospital (Ocean Park Master Redevelopment Project Contract CS01)','Vet Hospital','Ocean Park Corporation','Ocean Park Corporation','<p>The mojar element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the structure of the Veterinary Hospital including the Pool Block, Office Block &amp; Transformer Room</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation of architectural, E&amp;M, BS, Fire Services, Lift, MVAC &amp; the likes within the building of the Veterinary Hospital</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation of utility services to the new Veterinary Hospital including Fresh water, salt water, fire services water, control cables</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of drainage &amp; sewerage system for discharging storm water &amp; foul water to the existing system in the vicinity</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation, testing &amp; commissioning of a Life Support System at the Veterinary Hospital</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Transportation of facilities &amp; equipments from the existing Veterinary Hospital to the new Veterinary Hospital upon occupation</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:46:33.277000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.692000',NULL,8,36,'en',4.00),(9,'jn2g6g8nguhvddg5v01ksu2d','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A (Contract No. TP37/03)','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Civil and Engineering Development Department','29 June 2004 - 15 October 2008','<p>This is the engineering infrastructure project for Pak Shek Kok Development.  The major works of the project consisted of a significant quantity of site formation works; and the construction of roads &amp; bridges, cycle track, water front promenade, subway, and the associated landscaping works, etc.</p>','2025-06-03 03:47:41.938000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.683000',NULL,8,36,'en',5.00),(11,'v4pswur2x6g3j2ndsqv47uhe','Construction of Cherry Street Park at Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon (Contract No. SS M327)','Construction of Cherry Street Park at Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','31 December 2003 - 01 August 2005','<p>The works included the construction of an open space park of a total site area of approx. 40,100m2. Extremely demanding  architectural features and high standard finishes were required for the project. </p>','2025-06-03 03:48:58.135000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.763000',NULL,8,36,'en',6.00),(13,'x84dp3atl82w3omveld52shj','Construction of District Open Space in Areas 3 & 8, Tsing Yi, Hong Kong (Contract No. SS L345)','Construction of District Open Space in Areas 3 & 8, Tsing Yi, Hong Kong','Architectural Services Department','26 February 2003 - 24 June 2004','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Strategic planning was one of the key to the success of this project as some of the vegetations can only be planted during certain time of the year to ensure their sustainability.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Due to the site&#x27;s proximity to the general public, the safety, environmental impact, access with minimal distraction and interruption to the local community and security were the main concerns throughout the project.</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:49:59.408000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.682000',NULL,8,36,'en',7.00),(15,'dle2f82s25zz3w0uhmfa2guh','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-03 03:50:44.519000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.768000',NULL,8,36,'en',8.00),(17,'i34obn1bbgqjvo5n1a5k99bd','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T. (Contract No. RE G324)','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T.','Architectural Services Department Government of HKSAR','01 January 1998 - 27 August 1999','<p>A sports field, total site area approx. 42,000 m2 comprising running track, football field.</p><br/><p>Spectator stand with reinforced concrete structure and structural steel canopy with steel sheet cladding and piling foundations approx. 130m x 22m overall on plan and 16.8m high from ground level to the top of steel canopy.</p><br/><p>Completion of a partially completed sports complex comprising a sports field and a spectator stand.</p><br/><p>Soil, surface at er and sub-soil drainage.</p><br/><p>External works and ancillary buildings.</p><br/><p>Building services installation.</p><br/><p>Car park, planter, Emergency Vehicular Access (EVA), paving, fence wall, drainage works</p>','2025-06-03 03:52:06.111000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.731000',NULL,8,36,'en',9.00),(19,'yfopyano6zvzb9ef0q3qbuos','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon (Contract No. SS E362)','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','11 April 1997 - 26 March 1999','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The site formation includes a bulk excavation area of approximately 60,000m3. approximately 30% was rock excavation.</li><li>Construction of 250m long retaining walls with maximum height of 12m.</li><li>Construction of a 130m-long carriageway bridge on a slope.</li><li>Construction of a single storey service building (43mx12mx3.7m high) with changing rooms, toilets, booking office, storage room, general office, first aid room, staff room, plant rooms, open court, seating area, kiosk and breezeway.</li><li>External works comprising barrier walls, tennis courts, play area, jogging tracks, fitness stations, pavilion, pump rooms and fountains.</li><li>Landscaping works, car park, park furniture, drainage and plumbing works, M&amp;E works, water filtration and circulation installation.</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:53:24.330000','2025-07-07 08:00:27.432000',NULL,8,36,'en',10.00),(21,'qcc22r93681t0zrv11pgrzen','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan (Contract No. SS C410)','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan','Architectural Services Department','01 January 1995 - 02 January 1998','<p>Construction of two covered spectator stands together with drainage and waterworks, landscaping, M&amp;E works and sports facilities. </p>','2025-06-03 03:54:30.090000','2025-07-07 08:00:27.732000',NULL,8,36,'en',11.00),(23,'weolbo09vdr6yripk05j2n1p','港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池重置工程 (沙田至中環綫 – 合約編號1126)','港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池重置工程','香港鐵路有限公司','2014 年 01 月 20 日 - 2017 年 05 月 31 日','<p>沙田至中環綫是香港鐵路有限公司在九龍及港島區進行的長達17公里的鐵路擴建工程。 該項目涉及將鐵路由大圍延伸至紅磡及由紅磡延伸至金鐘段，中間連接多條現有鐵路路線。</p><p>由於沙中綫會展站設於舊有灣仔碼頭公共運輸交匯處、港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池的地底，而會展站須以明挖回填方式興建，舊有港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池需永久重置於南面停車場的位置。舊有設施會在新設施建成並投入服務後才拆卸。</p><p>工程項目包括興建一座新的港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池，建築物是一座有鋼桁架屋頂的5層高鋼筋混凝土樓房。工程還包括設計和建造大廈的外牆、內部結構和裝修、設備和裝置、屋宇裝備工程，其中包括起重橫樑和支撐細節，鋼結構通道平台，電氣，低壓電，過濾器，交流電，電梯，升降機和自動扶梯，煤氣, 水管和排水系統。</p>','2025-06-03 03:57:23.582000','2025-07-07 08:00:26.720000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',1.00),(25,'pe86y0lapp9x2l0vtoxtgrgm','香港仔港灣兩岸海濱長廊和鴨脷洲大街 一帶之美化工程 (合約編號CV/2011/02)','香港仔港灣兩岸海濱長廊和鴨脷洲大街 一帶之美化工程','土木工程拓展署','2011 年 09 月 30 日 - 2014 年 12 月 31 日','<p>香港仔兩岸海濱長廊和鴨脷洲大街一帶之美化工程採用設計與建造合約形式。本工程主旨為改善香港仔兩岸的旅遊設施，進一步突顯香港仔獨有的&quot;傳統漁港&quot;及本土文化特色，並加強多元化旅遊的元素，以提升香港仔對海外旅客及本地居民的吸引力。</p>','2025-06-03 04:01:36.591000','2025-07-07 08:00:28.143000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',2.00),(27,'fa8sc7djd739ez8xfnyetu5c','動感天地及冰極天地 (海洋公園主要重建項目合約CS03)','動感天地及冰極天地','海洋公園公司','2009 年 11 月 02 日 - 2012 年 07 月 08 日','<p>海洋公園展開「全新發展計劃」，並於高峰樂園建造兩個全新主題項目，分別為「動感天地」及「冰極天地」，總共佔地四十萬平方尺。</p><p>「動感天地」內有六個刺激機動遊戲及設施、遊戲攤位、美食餐廳及特別設計全新精品店等。「冰極天地」則由「北極之旅」、「南極奇觀」和「極地時速」過山車所組成。</p><p>工程用上大量特別建築材料包括製造冰山及模擬石的玻璃纖維增強混凝土。為了讓遊客能夠將極地的水底世界一覽無遺，展館特地採用了透明亞加力膠板及厚度達202mm的透明強化玻璃，建造水底遊客隧道及水底觀賞螢幕。新開設的冰極餐廳也用上了透明亞加力膠板作觀賞螢幕，讓遊客享受美食的同時也可以欣賞到南極企鵝。</p>','2025-06-03 04:03:07.417000','2025-07-07 08:00:28.128000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',3.00),(29,'hz456tzg5y2y1zcursvyrxim','海洋公園全新發展計劃 (合約CS01 –動物醫院)','海洋公園全新發展計劃','香港海洋公園','2007 年 03 月 26 日 - 2008 年 10 月 31 日','<p>工程主要包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>興建動物醫院的主體建築，包括游泳池，辦公大樓及變壓房</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>醫院內的機電，屋宇設備，消防，電梯，通風及空調系統的安裝及裝飾工程</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>醫院內安裝公用設施，包括食水，鹹水，消防水及操控電纜</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建立排水及排污系統使雨水及污水排放到附近的現有系統</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>醫院內安裝，檢测和测試生命維持系統</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>從現有的醫院運送設備與儀器到新的動物醫院</li></ul>','2025-06-03 04:04:29.499000','2025-07-07 08:00:28.103000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',4.00),